# Forge — git attributes.
#
# Union-merge for regenerated, line-oriented derived docs (multi-contributor
# safety). These files are GENERATED, never hand-edited (FORGE.md, Principle 6),
# and they are append-/line-oriented, so when two branches each add lines git's
# default merge produces a spurious conflict on every overlap. `merge=union`
# tells git to keep BOTH sides' lines instead of conflicting — eliminating the
# single most common merge conflict for parallel contributors.
#
# Union-merge can leave the lines slightly out of canonical order or duplicated.
# That is fine and self-healing: on ANY conflict (or after any merge) just
# regenerate the canonical form with `make forge-sync-docs` and commit — the
# generators are the only real writers of these files. See docs/guides/teams.md.
docs/generated/CHANGELOG.md   merge=union
docs/generated/traceability.md merge=union
prompts/STATUS.md             merge=union
